Bisi Kolawole on Wednesday emerged the candidate of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) in the June 18 governorship elec­tion in Ekiti State. Kolawole, former chairman of the PDP in Ekiti, trounced Se­gun Oni, a former governor, and Kolapo Olusola, a former deputy governor of the state. The results of the primary electionthattookplaceinAdo-Ek­iti are: Bisi Kolawole, 671; Kayode Adaramodu, 10; KazeemAyodeji, 6; Olusola Kolapo, 93; DeborahAli, 1; Ojo, 1; Makanjuola, 1; Biodun Olujimi, 2; AderemiAdewumi, 1; AdewaleAribisala, 56, andSegun Oni, 330. Court Declares Deductions From Federation Account For Police… West African Leaders To Hold Summit After Latest Coups Governor Udom Emmanuel of AkwaIbomwasthechairman of the primary election commit­tee. 183,000 APC Members In Ekiti To Elect Guber Candidate Today Meanwhile, about 183,000 membersof theAllProgressives Congress(APC) inEkitiStatewill today file out toelectthe governor­shipcandidateof thepartyforthe governorshipelectionscheduled for June 18. Governor Abubakar Badaru of Jigawa State who is the Chair­man of the APC Committee for EkitiGovernorshipPrimary, dis­closed this on Wednesday. Badaru, whospokeinAdoEk­iti, the Ekiti State capital, during interaction with the APC aspi­rants preparatory to the party’s governorshipprimaryholdingto­dayalsoassuredallaspirantsthat he would ensure a level playing ground so that a popular person would emerge as the APC gover­norship flag bearer. POLL He also disclosed that Option A4 direct primary would be adopted in conformity with the party’s guidelines to conduct the shadow poll, saying nothing will stophisresolvetoorganiseafree, fair, transparent and credible ex­ercise. “The party has a guideline in the conduct of direct primary, which is the accreditation of the party members after getting their voter cards and party member­ship slips carrying their photo­graphs and their names should alsobecontained intheparty reg­isters in their respective wards. “After this is done, the mem­bers 